comments: Niang (PHI) moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and absorbs the marginal body contact during the driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) briefly grasps and immediately releases Sims' (NYK) jersey as he receives the pass.
Sims (NYK) has his arm extended toward Embiid (PHI) and makes contact with Embiid's arm, which alters his jump shot attempt.
Maxey (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Brunson (NYK) at the end of the drive.
Maxey (PHI) makes clean contact with the ball and defects it away from Barrett (NYK) during the drive.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Replay review of the out of bounds called on Tucker (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Brunson (NYK) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Brunson (NYK) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Tucker (PHI) collapses his forearm as he moves alongside Barrett (NYK) and marginal contact occurs as they disengage after the gather on the driving shot attempt.
After Maxey (PHI) returns to the ground from his jump shot attempt, he drifts to his left and marginal contact occurs as Barrett (NYK) stops his forward momentum.

Harden (PHI) stops his forward momentum and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from Grimes (NYK) at the end of the drive. Any leg to leg contact with Grimes as Harden comes to a stop is deemed incidental.
Tucker (PHI) adjusts to Randle's (NYK) path and incidental foot to foot contact occurs as Randle inadvertently steps on his foot when they come together on the perimeter.
Embiid (PHI) contests the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (NYK) extended leg after the release.
